                            <comment id="12597300" author="joshrotenberg" created="Thu, 15 May 2008 22:32:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch fixes the issue for me. As an aside, if open() has not yet been called, the following error occurs:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can&apos;t call method &quot;handles&quot; on an undefined value at /usr/local/lib/perl5/site_perl/5.8.8/Thrift/Socket.pm line 87.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because $self-&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
{handle}
&lt;p&gt; is undef until open is called. The patch should handle both cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
